                        <h1 class="entry-title single-blog-title">Mayors Call on Govt to Withdraw Decision Halving Local Business Tax</h1>                        <div class="single-author">
                            <span class="author">
                              <a href="https://hungarytoday.hu/author/mti-hungary-today/">MTI-Hungary Today</a>
                               2020.12.21.                        </div>
                                            </div>
                <div class="row">
                                      <div class="col-md-8 single-news-elements " style="border-color:#71b3f7;">
                                                    <img width="2048" height="1415" src="https://hungarytoday.hu/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/D_NOE20191212020.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="https://hungarytoday.hu/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/D_NOE20191212020.jpg 2048w, https://hungarytoday.hu/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/D_NOE20191212020-300x207.jpg 300w, https://hungarytoday.hu/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/D_NOE20191212020-768x531.jpg 768w, https://hungarytoday.hu/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/D_NOE20191212020-1024x707.jpg 1024w, https://hungarytoday.hu/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/D_NOE20191212020-575x397.jpg 575w" sizes="(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px" />                        
                        <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Budapest Mayor Gergely Karácsony and 37 mayors of Budapest districts and cities around Hungary <a href="https://ado.hu/ado/szamos-polgarmester-tiltakozik-a-hipa-dontes-miatt/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">demanded</a> in a joint statement on Sunday that the government withdraw a decision on halving the local business tax.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The statement issued by an organisation dubbed Alliance of Free Cities said the move would be a &#8220;final blow&#8221; to local councils.</p>
<blockquote>
<h3 style="text-align: justify;">&#8220;It has nothing to do with managing the economic crisis but is about the power politics of Fidesz,&#8221;</h3>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;">the statement added. The mayors signing the statement called for joint protests by local councils that want to &#8220;protect the public services they offer to citizens and their ability to take action&#8221;.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">As a sign of protest, the mayors said their cities would turn off their festive holiday lights from 7pm on December 23 in order to call people&#8217;s attention to the importance of public services offered by the councils.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The councils use local business tax revenues throughout Hungary to ensure public services, local transport, rubbish collection, road maintenance, public lighting and the care of green areas, they said. The revenues are also used for paying social support, financing theatres and other cultural and sport activities, they added.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The mayors said they expect that the compensation <a href="https://hungarytoday.hu/coronavirus-government-supplements-economic-protection-action-plan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">promised</a> by Prime Minister Viktor Orbán to cities with more than 25,000 residents would be distributed arbitrarily, on a political basis.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>featured image illustration (PMO Chief Gulyás and Budapest Mayor Karácsony); via Noémi Bruzák/MTI</em></p>

